just_use markdown.go

# label: CLEAN_INFRA
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Zulip-flavored markdown: goldmark (CommonMark + GFM) with pre-processing
for @**Name**, #**Channel**, #**Channel>Topic**, #**Channel>Topic@MsgID**
and post-processing to attach image previews under /user_uploads/* links.

WithUnsafe() is deliberate: the pre-processor emits inline HTML spans for
mentions/links that goldmark would otherwise strip. Safe because the only
unsafe content is what we generated from matched regexes — user markdown
still runs through the sanitized path. Unknown names/channels fall through
unchanged (goldmark renders the **bold** naturally).
